A Philanthropist and Managing Director/CEO, Spectra Industries Limited Mr. Duro Kuteyi has predicted that tough times lie ahead, post COVID-19, with a plea on governments to brace up for the worst and plan ahead against food crisis. He said only massive food production and processing would prevent scarcity that is looming ahead for the country Kuteyi, who spoke in his office on Sunday, said the pandemic is a warning of an impending because, which may lead to a shortage of food, scarcity of essential commodities and loss of job among others. Kuteyi’s firm, Spectra distributed food palliatives and the company’s nutritional products to the six states of Lagos, Ogun, Oyo, Osun, Ondo and Ekiti to help fight COVID-19 and the aftermath of the lockdown on the people of Southwest.